{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567490","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567490"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T00:02:57+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T00:02:57+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"19087"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"19087","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/19087"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.11,0.03,0.06,0.75,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11821"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"87430"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11821","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11821"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"19087"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"71649"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"8"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"27"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4963"},{"type":"tags","id":"8770"},{"type":"tags","id":"11636"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27775"},{"type":"contributions","id":"29701"},{"type":"contributions","id":"29702"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44008"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44743"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"87430","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/87430"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 22-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic for a pre-employment medical examination for a position as a commercial pilot. He has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. On examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate test to screen for colour vision deficiency?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Farnsworth-Munsell 100 hue test","Worth four-dot test","Amsler grid","Ishihara test","Hardy-Rand-Rittler plates"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EColour vision deficiency affects approximately 8% of males and 0.5% of females, with red-green deficiency being the most common type.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003EIshihara test\u003C/strong\u003E is the most widely used screening tool for colour vision deficiency. It consists of a series of pseudoisochromatic plates containing coloured dots that form numbers or patterns. It is particularly effective at detecting red-green colour deficiency, which is the most common form of colour blindness. The test is quick, reliable, and suitable for screening in primary care settings.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003EHardy-Rand-Rittler plates\u003C/strong\u003E are another type of pseudoisochromatic test that can detect blue-yellow as well as red-green deficiencies. While useful, they are less commonly available and not considered the first-line screening tool.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003EAmsler grid\u003C/strong\u003E is used to detect central visual field defects or distortions, particularly in macular degeneration. It consists of a grid of horizontal and vertical lines and does not assess colour vision.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003EWorth four-dot test\u003C/strong\u003E is used to assess binocular vision and suppression. It involves viewing red and green lights through red-green glasses but is not designed to detect colour vision deficiency.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003EFarnsworth-Munsell 100 hue test\u003C/strong\u003E is a comprehensive colour vision test that requires arranging coloured caps in order of hue. While it provides detailed information about colour discrimination, it is time-consuming and typically reserved for specialist assessment rather than screening.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The Ishihara test is the most widely used screening tool for red-green colour vision deficiency.","Colour vision deficiency affects approximately 8% of males and 0.5% of females.","Colour vision testing is essential for certain occupations including pilots, electricians, and train drivers."],"references":["Pandey N, Chandrakar AK, Garg ML. Tests for color vision deficiency: Is it time to revise the standards? Indian J Ophthalmol. 2015 Sep;63(9):752-3. Available at: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC4705720/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"71649"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"19087"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"71649","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/71649"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-02-27T23:17:04+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-02-27T23:17:04+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11821"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"87430"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"8","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/8"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc41","name":"Ophthalmology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id"